	<exercise>
		<problem>
			<para>Given: the following matrices <latex>A</latex> and <latex>B</latex>, answer the questions below. If the specified matrix operation is defined, compute the answer.</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
					A\ =\ [1\ \ -5\ \ -4\ \ 1] \qquad \qquad
					B\ =\ \left[\begin{array}{r} -6 \\ 0 \\ 3 \\ -9 \end{array}\right]
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</problem>
		
		<part>
			<problem><para>What kind of matrix is <latex>A</latex>?</para></problem>
			<approach>
				<answer><para><latex>A</latex> is a row matrix of size <latex>(1,4)</latex>.</para></answer>
			</approach>
		</part>
		
		<part>
			<problem><para>What kind of matrix is <latex>B</latex>?</para></problem>
			<approach><answer><para><latex>B</latex> is a column matrix of size <latex>(4,1)</latex>.</para></answer></approach>
		</part>
		
		<part>
			<problem><para>Is <latex>AB</latex> defined? if not, why not?</para></problem>
			<approach>
				<solution>
					<para>The matrix product is <latex>AB</latex> is defined because the number of columns of <latex>A</latex> equals the number of rows of <latex>B</latex>: both numbers are equal to <latex>4</latex>. The resulting matrix has size <latex>(1,1)</latex>:</para>
					
					<math.display>
						<latex>AB\ =\ [1\cdot (-6) + (-5)\cdot 0 + (-4)\cdot 3 + 1\cdot (-9)]\ =\ [-27]</latex>
					</math.display>
				</solution>
			</approach>
		</part>
		
		<part>
			<problem><para>Is <latex>BA</latex> defined? If not, why not?</para></problem>
			<approach>
				<solution>
					<para>The matrix product <latex>BA</latex> is defined because the number of columns of <latex>B</latex> equals the number of rows of <latex>A</latex>. The resulting matrix has size <latex>(4,4)</latex>:</para>
					
					<math.display>
						<latex>
							<![CDATA[
							BA\ =\ 
							\left[\begin{array}{rrrr}
							-6 & 30 & 24 & -12 \\
							0  &   0  &  0  &  0  \\
							3 & -15 & -12 & 6 \\
							-9 & 45 & 36 & -18
							\end{array}\right]
							]]>
						</latex>
					</math.display>
				</solution>
			</approach>
		</part>
		
		<part>
			<problem><para>Find <latex>A^T</latex> and <latex>B^T</latex>.</para></problem>
			<approach>
				<answer>
					<computation>
						<left>A^T</left>
						<center>=</center>
						<right>
							<![CDATA[
							\left[\begin{array}{r}
							1 \\ -5 \\ -4 \\ 1
							\end{array}\right]
							]]>
						</right>
						<left>B^T</left>
						<center>=</center>
						<right>[-6\ \ 0\ \ 3\ \ -9 ]</right>
					</computation>
				</answer>
			</approach>
		</part>
		
		<part>
			<problem><para>Is <latex>A^TB^T</latex> defined? If not, why not?</para></problem>
			<approach>
				<solution>
					<para><latex>A^T</latex> has <latex>1</latex> column, and <latex>B^T</latex> has <latex>1</latex> row. As these two numbers are equal, the required product is defined. The resulting matrix has size <latex>(4,4)</latex>:</para>
					
					<computation>
						<left>A^T\cdot B^T</left>
						<center>=</center>
						<right>
							<![CDATA[
							[1\ \ -5\ \ -4\ \ 2]^T \cdot \left[\begin{array}{r} -6 \\ 0 \\ 3 \\ -9 \end{array}\right]^T
							]]>
						</right>
						<left></left>
						<center>=</center>
						<right>
							<![CDATA[
							\left[\begin{array}{r} 1 \\ -5 \\ -4 \\ 2 \end{array}\right] \cdot [-6\ \ 0\ \ 3\ \ -9]
							]]>
						</right>
						<left></left>
						<center>=</center>
						<right>
							<![CDATA[
							\left[\begin{array}{rrrr}
							-6 & 0 & 3 & -9 \\
							30 & 0 & -15 & 45 \\
							-24 & 0 & -12 & 36 \\
							-12 & 0 & 6 & -18
							\end{array}\right]
							]]>
						</right>
					</computation>
				</solution>
			</approach>
		</part>
		
		<part>
			<problem><para>Is <latex>B^TA^T</latex> defined? If not, why not?</para></problem>
			<approach>
				<solution>
					<para><latex>B^T</latex> has <latex>4</latex> columns, while <latex>A^T</latex> has <latex>4</latex> rows. The product <latex>B^TA^T</latex> is defined because these two numbers are equal. The resulting matrix will have size <latex>(1,1)</latex>:</para>
					
					<computation>
						<left>B^TA^T</left>
						<center>=</center>
						<right>
							<![CDATA[
							\left[\begin{array}{r} -6 \\ 0 \\ 3 \\ -9 \end{array}\right]^T \cdot [1\ \ -5\ \ -4\ \ 2]^T
							]]>
						</right>
						<left></left>
						<center>=</center>
						<right>
							<![CDATA[
							[-6\ \ 0\ \ 3\ \ -9] \cdot \left[\begin{array}{r} 1 \\ -5 \\ -4 \\ 2 \end{array}\right]
							]]>
						</right>
						<left></left>
						<center>=</center>
						<right>[ -36 ]</right>
					</computation>
				</solution>
			</approach>
		</part>
	</exercise>
